# This script 
this script extract from a given facebook's page name, all posts related to a subject, 
since public feed in facebook is restricted, this solution gives only posts in a given page

## Use:
### requirement:

to run this script you need to have facebook-scraper python package installed ( pip install facebook-scraper)
you need also pymongo installed ( pip -m install pymongo[srv])
### config_mongodb
define your connection string to the mongodb 
if you have the entire string, you just paste it in conn_str
else, if you use ATLAS, you need to provide a username, password and database name 
### config_query
define the subject you are looknig for in config_query file, give the page to look in,
the maximum number of posts to extract and a verbose parameter to choose if you want explicit 
progress in console ! 
